                                <h2 class="m-t0">What is FOTA?</h2>
                                <p>FOTA (Firmware Over-the-Air) is a technology that allows operators of
                                    Internet-connected devices to remotely and seamlessly upgrade firmware version
                                    without requiring physical intervention on the device. The ability to update the
                                    operating system of your connected assets is essential to keeping your devices
                                    secure, adding new features, and fixing bugs.</p>

                                <h3 class="m-t0">What do you stand to gain with FOTA? </h3>

                                <p>Before IoT platforms began offering firmware over-the-air upgrade services,
                                    reprogramming of all devices would have to be done manually time consuming,
                                    inefficient and sometimes prohibitive. or not at all. In this way, a connected fleet
                                    would become obsolete for months (or years) and become more vulnerable to malicious
                                    attackers became.</p>
                                <p>This is why his FOTA was adopted as the new way to update firmware. Modern and Secure
                                    IoT Devices IoT business owners don't just easily manage their devices remotely with
                                    the powerful firmware distribution tool .</p>
